T√≠tulo: Project APB ‚Äî Learning Through Play

Descri√ß√£o Curta (2‚Äì3 linhas):
A hands-on STEAM project designed to help teens explore computing concepts through creativity and interactive activities.

Context / Problem:

Teens often find programming abstract and intimidating.

Goal: create a playful, interactive learning experience that makes programming tangible.

My Role:

UX design, interaction flow, prototyping, visual layout

Conducted informal user research with teens

Iterated on prototypes based on observations and feedback

Process:

Research & Insights

Observed how teens interacted with previous STEAM kits.

Identified pain points: lack of immediate feedback, complex instructions.

Ideation

Brainstormed playful interaction concepts.

Selected ideas that balance learning, engagement, and simplicity.

Prototyping

Paper prototypes ‚Üí Digital wireframes ‚Üí Interactive Figma prototype

Tested with 5 teens and collected feedback.

Visual Design

Bright, playful colors to signal fun

Simple typography for clarity

Icons and cues for interaction

Outcomes / Lessons Learned:

Teens responded positively to immediate feedback and gamified interactions

Learned to balance guidance with exploration

Would add adaptive difficulty levels next iteration

